<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Monster1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Monster,</orth> subst. an unnatural and deformed creature: <bibl n="shak. son 114.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 114, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.314" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 314</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 31</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 31</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 31</bibl> 148 etc. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 12</bibl>. 21 etc. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.1.196" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 196</bibl>. 199 etc. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 2, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 2, 82</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 6</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.23" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.155" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.798" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 798</bibl> <cit><quote>(will break the back of man, the heart of m.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.293" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 293</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 33</bibl>. H4B Ind. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 33</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 81</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.146" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 146</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.146" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 146</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.190" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.8.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 8, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 1, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.161" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.5.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 5, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.161" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 63</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.3.70" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 70</bibl>. Per. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.0." default="NO" valid="yes">IV Prol. 12</bibl>. In a moral sense: <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.85" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 3, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 4, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.102" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 2, 2</bibl>. Peculiar passage: <cit><quote>as if there were some m. in his thought too hideous to be shown,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 107</bibl></cit> (== something monstrous).
